  "chapter": {
    "number": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Taming the Tongue"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Not many of you should become teachers, my brothers, because you know that we who teach will be judged more strictly."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "We all stumble in many ways. If anyone is never at fault in what he says, he is a perfect man, able to control his whole body."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "When we put bits into the mouths of horses to make them obey us, we can guide the whole animal."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "Consider ships as well. Although they are so large and are driven by strong winds, they are steered by a very small rudder wherever the pilot is inclined."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "In the same way, the tongue is a small part of the body, but it boasts of great things. Consider how small a spark sets a great forest ablaze."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "The tongue also is a fire, a world of wickedness among the parts of the body. It pollutes the whole person, sets the course of his life on fire, and is itself set on fire by hell.",
          {
            "noteId": 2768
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "All kinds of animals, birds, reptiles, and creatures of the sea are being tamed and have been tamed by man,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "but no man can tame the tongue. It is a restless evil, full of deadly poison."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "With the tongue we bless our Lord and Father, and with it we curse men, who have been made in Godâ€™s likeness."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "Out of the same mouth come blessing and cursing. My brothers, this should not be!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "Can both fresh water and salt water",
          {
            "noteId": 2769
          },
          "flow from the same spring?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "My brothers, can a fig tree grow olives, or a grapevine bear figs? Neither can a salt spring",
          {
            "noteId": 2770
          },
          "produce fresh water."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Wisdom from Above"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "Who is wise and understanding among you? Let him show it by his good conduct, by deeds done in the humility that comes from wisdom."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "But if you harbor bitter jealousy and selfish ambition in your hearts, do not boast in it or deny the truth."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "Such wisdom does not come from above, but is earthly, unspiritual, demonic."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "For where jealousy and selfish ambition exist, there will be disorder and every evil practice."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "But the wisdom from above is first of all pure, then peace-loving, gentle, accommodating, full of mercy and good fruit, impartial, and sincere."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "Peacemakers who sow in peace reap the fruit of righteousness.",
          {
            "noteId": 2771
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
